---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
import { docsNavigation } from '../../data/docsNavigation';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Neuwerk Documentation"
  description="Operator-focused documentation for deploying, configuring, running, and integrating Neuwerk."
>
  <p>
    These docs are organized by operator workflow. If you are evaluating Neuwerk locally, start
    with the Vagrant demo. If you are onboarding for a production-style environment, start from the
    released cloud image path.
  </p>

  <p>
    The primary runtime artifact is the Neuwerk appliance image. The Vagrant path is the fastest
    local loop. The cloud-image path is the baseline for first-time cloud onboarding before
    autoscaling rollout work.
  </p>

  <h2 id="recommended-structure">How To Use These Docs</h2>
  <p>
    If you want a local single-VM demo first, begin with <a
    href="/docs/tutorials/run-the-vagrant-demo-box">Run The Vagrant Demo Box</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    For production-style onboarding, use <a
    href="/docs/tutorials/launch-from-released-cloud-image">Launch Neuwerk From The Released Cloud Image</a>.
    After the node is running, continue with <a
    href="/docs/tutorials/create-your-first-policy">Create Your First Policy</a> to validate policy
    flow end-to-end.
  </p>

  <p>
    Before ASG, VMSS, or MIG based rollouts, read <a
    href="/docs/architecture/cloud-rollout-integration">Cloud Rollout Integration</a> so lifecycle
    behavior and rollout boundaries are explicit.
  </p>

  <p>
    The concepts pages describe the control-plane and dataplane split, policy behavior, DNS
    enforcement, TLS inspection, cluster replication, and observability. Those pages are where to
    go when you need to understand why the Neuwerk behaves a certain way before making a change.
  </p>

  <div class="not-prose mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
    {docsNavigation.map((section) => (
      <section class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900/60 p-5">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white">{section.title}</h3>
        <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-slate-400">
          {section.title === 'Getting Started' && 'Guided paths for a local Vagrant demo, cloud-image onboarding, and first policy authoring.'}
          {section.title === 'How-To Guides' && 'Task-focused instructions for access, policy authoring, safer rollout, upgrades, integrations, and recovery work.'}
          {section.title === 'Concepts' && 'Conceptual pages that explain Neuwerk behavior, boundaries, tradeoffs, and operational switches.'}
          {section.title === 'Reference' && 'Precise schemas, endpoints, interfaces, and fixed protocol details.'}
          {section.title === 'Community' && 'Release process, OSS launch status, contribution expectations, and security reporting.'}
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-300">
          {section.items.map((item) => (
            <li>
              <a href={item.href} class="transition-colors hover:text-white">
                {item.label}
              </a>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </section>
    ))}
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
